observationText: The ST88-3 cell line expresses the EGF receptor but not the GGF receptor, in contrast to the 88-14 and 90-8 lines which express both receptors.
The ST88-3 cell line had increased expression of miR-135b and miR-889, which were shown to induce Wnt signaling and promote invasion when inhibited by antisense inhibitors in this cell line.
